choices.text:
finding a job, support and finding cliques of people to socialize with in the community or through hobbies.
I don't party or drink, those aren't my kinda things. I just wanna have friends and experience stuff. But I feel like I've been stuck at a job I don't like for over 5 years and I have to surround myself with people I hate to keep the job. 

With this pandemic we can't really hang out like we used to. The cafes of course are closed but moreso the ones that have space for camping, barbeques, board games etc. They're closed too. Even hanging with friends has gotten complicated. No sooner am I meeting someone i get notified of a "I have covid test and I tested +, I'll be quarantined for 14days" or "I've been coughing. Please inform your friends i was with so they can get tested." This sucks.

The biggest issue I've been having is my co-workers of course. They've grown sour on me during the pandemic. The pandemic, forcing us to work with masks, limiting social activities has brought other tensions to the surface. And now I'm on the receiving end of it. Forcibly socially distant from my friends to the distance one would restrict from their families, is cruelly enforced in my work.

The worst thing Colin happened was a Covid touch of mine, infected everyone in my team and coworking chain. Many tried to turn it around on
